A vintage 1960s psychedelic concert poster style illustration featuring a massive coffee bean transforming into a glowing microprocessor chip, surrounded by swirling peace symbols and flower power motifs in vibrant orange, purple, and electric blue. The chip floats above a retro-futuristic wristwatch with vacuum tubes and circuit boards visible inside its face. Radiating sunburst patterns emanate from the central imagery, with delicate paisley patterns and Art Nouveau curves framing the composition. The color palette shifts from warm amber and gold tones to cool cosmic purples, evoking both the warmth of coffee and the electric energy of technology, all rendered in the distinctive screen-printed aesthetic of Haight-Ashbury era poster art.
